      "description": "Wells Fargo makes paying your auto loan easy from automatic payments to paying online, over the phone, or in person. Pay your way with Wells Fargo.",
      "keywords": "pay auto loan, pay car loan, how to make car payments, how do you make a car payment, how to pay my car payment",
      "inLanguage": "en",
      "name": "How to make car payments and pay your Wells Fargo auto loan | Wells Fargo",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_0_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "Can I make my car payment in advance?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_0_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "You can pay your account up to 3 months in advance. When you pay more than the total amount due, on or before the due date, the additional amount will pay down your principal balance and will also be applied to your next payment due. After your loan is paid ahead 3 months, any additional payments will be applied to the principal balance. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_1_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "How do I set up, change, or cancel automatic loan payments?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_1_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "To set up automatic payments, sign on, select your auto loan from Account Summary, and then select Set up Autopay.Opens a modal dialog for footnote 2 You can also call us at 1-800-289-8004 or download the automatic loan payments authorization (PDF), complete the form, and return by mail or fax. If you'd like to change your automatic payment, you'll need to cancel the recurring schedule and then set up Autopay again. To cancel your automatic payments, sign on, select your auto loan from Account Summary, and then select Manage Autopay. Please allow at least 3 business days before the automatic payment is scheduled to withdraw."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_2_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "How do I change my payment due date?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_2_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "Before you apply for a due date change, you'll need to meet the following criteria:  You've made the first payment on your auto loan. Your requested payment due date shouldn't be more than 15 days from your existing payment due date. For example, if your existing due date is the 5th of the month, you can change it to the 20th of the month, or any day in between. This is your first payment due date change. (You're allowed one payment due date change for the entire term of the loan.) Your account is current or no more than 10 days past due.  If you change your due date, your loan maturity date will be adjusted. Your monthly payment amount will remain the same. To request a due date change, please call us at 1-800-289-8004."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_3_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "Where can I find my payoff amount for my auto loan?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/auto-loans/make-payments/#Highlight20251015194248163-32952_3_AboutPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "Online Sign on, select your auto loan from Account Summary, and then Get payoff quote. Account statement  View your payoff amount and daily interest on your monthly account statement. Phone  Call us at 1-800-289-8004 to get an automated payoff quote or to speak to a representative. If you choose to pay off your account after the date provided, please call us for an updated quote."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
